00:15:02.026 --> 00:15:03.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll wait a little bit,

145
00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:07.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
just to see what they're like,
because they look a bit strange.

146
00:15:07.657 --> 00:15:09.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles] The children do?

147
00:15:09.575 --> 00:15:11.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, and the farmers.

148
00:15:11.744 --> 00:15:12.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What sort of strange?

149
00:15:13.413 --> 00:15:14.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

150
00:15:17.708 --> 00:15:18.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

151
00:15:20.336 --> 00:15:21.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Vegetables.

152
00:15:23.172 --> 00:15:24.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There.

153
00:15:28.886 --> 00:15:30.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bruno, have you unpacked everything?

154
00:15:30.346 --> 00:15:32.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I think you should go back
upstairs and finish off.

155
00:15:36.394 --> 00:15:37.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, ma'am.

156
00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:43.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Elsa] Bruno.

157
00:15:43.901 --> 00:15:45.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I told you they were strange.

158
00:15:45.528 --> 00:15:47.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Who?
-The farmers.

159
00:15:47.697 --> 00:15:48.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They wear pajamas.

160
00:15:57.540 --> 00:16:01.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

161
00:16:03.546 --> 00:16:04.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

162
00:16:06.549 --> 00:16:08.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, Bruno, I was just coming
to look for you.

163
00:16:09.844 --> 00:16:11.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, thank you for that.
That was extremely useful.

164
00:16:11.846 --> 00:16:14.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I'll be over to see you later.
-Of course, Herr <i>Kommandant.</i>

165
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:16.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] Come in.

166
00:16:21.397 --> 00:16:22.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sit down, sit down.

167
00:16:24.442 --> 00:16:25.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, what do you think?

168
00:16:28.571 --> 00:16:29.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, dear.

169
00:16:30.448 --> 00:16:31.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I want to go home.

170
00:16:33.868 --> 00:16:35.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are home, Bruno.

171
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:38.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Home is where the family is.
Isn't that right?

172
00:16:41.709 --> 00:16:45.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bruno, you have to at least give
the place a chance.

173
00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:47.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I promise you,
it won't be long before you--

174
00:16:47.673 --> 00:16:49.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why do the farmers wear pajamas?

175
00:16:50.801 --> 00:16:52.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can see them from my window.

176
00:17:01.103 --> 00:17:02.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The thing is, Bruno…

177
00:17:04.106 --> 00:17:05.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
those people…

178
00:17:06.484 --> 00:17:09.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, you see,
they're not really people at all.

179
00:17:09.654 --> 00:17:11.781 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

180
00:17:14.951 --> 00:17:17.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bruno, who told you it was a farm?
Was it Maria?

181
00:17:17.453 --> 00:17:18.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] No.

182
00:17:18.955 --> 00:17:20.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is a farm, isn't it?

183
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:23.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Elsa] Yes.

184
00:17:26.003 --> 00:17:27.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] Is it to do with your new job?

185
00:17:28.422 --> 00:17:30.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All you need to know
about my work here, Bruno,

186
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:35.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is that it's very important
to our country, and to you.

187
00:17:35.888 --> 00:17:39.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're working very hard to make this world
a better place for you to grow up in.

188
00:17:39.767 --> 00:17:42.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you're not a farmer. You're a soldier.

189
00:17:42.812 --> 00:17:45.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bruno, can you come and help me finish
sorting out in the kitchen?

190
00:17:46.232 --> 00:17:49.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can still play with them, though?
The children.

191
00:17:50.736 --> 00:17:52.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Elsa] I don't think so, Bruno. No. I…

192
00:17:52.947 --> 00:17:56.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Like you say, they're a bit strange.
A bit, um…

193
00:17:56.826 --> 00:17:57.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, they're different.

194
00:17:59.579 --> 00:18:00.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't worry, my darling. [kisses]

195
00:18:00.955 --> 00:18:03.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll find you some new friends,
but they won't be the ones from the farm.

196
00:18:05.334 --> 00:18:07.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ralf, you promised.
You said it was miles away.

197
00:18:07.878 --> 00:18:11.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It is. How was I to know he could see it
from the bedroom window?

198
00:18:11.507 --> 00:18:13.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There was one of them in our kitchen.

199
00:18:14.969 --> 00:18:16.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[sighs]
-[page rustling]

200
00:18:16.846 --> 00:18:18.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[instrumental music playing]

201
00:18:20.016 --> 00:18:20.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[pen scrapes]

202
00:18:22.768 --> 00:18:24.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds chirping]

203
00:18:38.034 --> 00:18:39.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicks tongue, sighs]

204
00:18:40.703 --> 00:18:42.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

205
00:18:43.539 --> 00:18:44.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno chuckles]

206
00:18:48.711 --> 00:18:50.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

207
00:18:55.343 --> 00:18:58.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Master Bruno, how are you today?
-Fed up.

208
00:18:58.596 --> 00:19:02.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. You said the same thing
every day for two whole weeks.

209
00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:03.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] It's true.

210
00:19:03.851 --> 00:19:06.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Maria] Well, you should be out playing.
-Playing with who?

211
00:19:06.854 --> 00:19:09.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I don't know. Gretel?
-[blows raspberries]

212
00:19:09.565 --> 00:19:12.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs] Well, you can make your own fun.

213
00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:14.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's what I'm trying to do.

214
00:19:15.196 --> 00:19:16.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One thing's for sure.

215
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:19.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sitting around being miserable
won't make things any happier.

216
00:19:21.869 --> 00:19:24.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno mimicking airplane engine rumbling]

217
00:19:26.415 --> 00:19:28.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[instrumental music playing]

218
00:20:08.582 --> 00:20:10.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

219
00:20:11.794 --> 00:20:13.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[gasps]
-[Elsa] Bruno, what are you doing?

220
00:20:14.213 --> 00:20:17.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Bruno] Exploring.
-No! No, not in the back.

221
00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:19.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you, it's out of bounds.
Explore at the front.

222
00:20:19.885 --> 00:20:21.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I've explored it all.

223
00:20:21.846 --> 00:20:24.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Well, find something else to do.
-Like what?

224
00:20:25.725 --> 00:20:27.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come back in now,
and we'll think of something.

225
00:20:32.106 --> 00:20:33.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[waltz music playing]

226
00:20:37.361 --> 00:20:40.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[radio static]
-[soft music playing]

227
00:20:53.544 --> 00:20:54.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cutlery clinking]

228
00:20:57.131 --> 00:20:58.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, children, what are you doing today?

229
00:20:59.300 --> 00:21:00.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Same as yesterday.

230
00:21:00.634 --> 00:21:02.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Ralf] And what was that?
-Same as the day before.

231
00:21:03.012 --> 00:21:04.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Except you went exploring.

232
00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:07.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I like exploring.

233
00:21:07.433 --> 00:21:08.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] Where did you go?

234
00:21:08.684 --> 00:21:11.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wanted to look in the back garden,
but Mom wouldn't let me.

235
00:21:12.855 --> 00:21:16.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The back garden?
Well, God forbid. [scoffs]

236
00:21:16.776 --> 00:21:18.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I expect you'll be missing
those friends of yours.

237
00:21:18.652 --> 00:21:20.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I even miss school.

238
00:21:20.488 --> 00:21:21.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

239
00:21:22.323 --> 00:21:24.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I never thought
I'd hear you say that.

240
00:21:25.409 --> 00:21:27.411 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Anyway, you won't be missing it for long.
-Really?

241
00:21:28.537 --> 00:21:30.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] I've arranged a tutor for you both.

242
00:21:31.248 --> 00:21:33.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A Herr Liszt
will be visiting twice a week.

243
00:21:35.127 --> 00:21:37.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] So, we're not going to school?

244
00:21:40.049 --> 00:21:41.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-School's coming here?
-[Ralf] Mm-hmm.

245
00:21:42.843 --> 00:21:45.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On an old bicycle, I gather.

246
00:21:46.180 --> 00:21:47.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Elsa] Hmm.

247
00:21:49.683 --> 00:21:51.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[birds chirping]
-[soft music playing]

248
00:22:03.447 --> 00:22:04.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[whispering] It's a poem about you.
-Hmm.

249
00:22:06.742 --> 00:22:07.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[giggles]

250
00:22:11.872 --> 00:22:12.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[water splashes]

251
00:22:25.970 --> 00:22:27.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

252
00:22:30.140 --> 00:22:31.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[sighs]
-Good morning, little man.

253
00:22:32.935 --> 00:22:34.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And how are you this morning?

254
00:22:35.020 --> 00:22:36.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can I ask you a favor?

255
00:22:37.147 --> 00:22:38.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Kurt] Well, you can ask.
-[Gretel chuckles]

256
00:22:39.567 --> 00:22:41.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are there any spare tires around?

257
00:22:42.194 --> 00:22:44.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
An old one from one
of the trucks or something?

258
00:22:44.697 --> 00:22:47.408 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, the only spare tire
I've seen around here

259
00:22:47.575 --> 00:22:49.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
belongs to Lieutenant Meinberg.

260
00:22:49.451 --> 00:22:50.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Gretel chuckling]

261
00:22:51.620 --> 00:22:53.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Gretel chuckling]

262
00:22:55.666 --> 00:22:57.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, is he using it?

263
00:22:57.334 --> 00:22:58.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, he's very attached to it.

264
00:22:58.878 --> 00:22:59.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Gretel chuckling]

265
00:22:59.962 --> 00:23:02.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] Oh, stop it.
He doesn't understand. He's only eight.

266
00:23:03.090 --> 00:23:06.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're only 12.
So, stop pretending you're any older.

267
00:23:08.512 --> 00:23:10.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you want a tire for anyway?

268
00:23:10.598 --> 00:23:12.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I want to make a swing.
-A swing?

269
00:23:13.642 --> 00:23:15.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That does sound exciting.

270
00:23:21.901 --> 00:23:22.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You!

271
00:23:22.902 --> 00:23:24.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[dog barking]

272
00:23:24.653 --> 00:23:25.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here, now.

273
00:23:28.574 --> 00:23:29.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Move!

274
00:23:30.618 --> 00:23:32.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[dog barking]

275
00:23:32.828 --> 00:23:34.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take this boy to the outhouse
in the back garden.

276
00:23:35.956 --> 00:23:38.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There are some tires in there.
He will select one.

277
00:23:38.125 --> 00:23:40.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You will carry it where he asks.
Do you understand?

278
00:23:43.380 --> 00:23:44.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps receding]

279
00:23:45.424 --> 00:23:47.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, little man,
what are you waiting for?

280
00:23:53.182 --> 00:23:54.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[tense music playing]

281
00:24:23.754 --> 00:24:26.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[flies buzzing]

282
00:24:32.012 --> 00:24:33.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How about this one?

283
00:24:42.231 --> 00:24:44.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[rope creaking]

284
00:25:01.834 --> 00:25:03.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[groans]
-[body thuds]

285
00:25:07.339 --> 00:25:08.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music fades]

286
00:25:08.507 --> 00:25:10.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

287
00:25:21.353 --> 00:25:22.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where's my mum?

288
00:25:23.689 --> 00:25:25.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh. She's out.

289
00:25:27.026 --> 00:25:29.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-When is she back?
-Soon, I expect.

290
00:25:30.863 --> 00:25:31.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But don't worry.

291
00:25:34.324 --> 00:25:35.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I might bleed to death.

292
00:25:37.036 --> 00:25:38.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, you won't.

293
00:25:42.708 --> 00:25:44.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[scissor snapping]

294
00:25:44.877 --> 00:25:47.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Bruno] Will I need to go to hospital?
-No.

295
00:25:48.297 --> 00:25:49.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's only a small cut.

296
00:25:51.133 --> 00:25:52.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[inhales sharply]

297
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, come on. It's not that bad.

298
00:25:55.888 --> 00:25:56.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There.

299
00:25:58.557 --> 00:25:59.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All better.

300
00:26:09.610 --> 00:26:12.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[box clatters]
-What's your name?

301
00:26:14.323 --> 00:26:15.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pavel.

302
00:26:16.867 --> 00:26:18.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, you've got to sit still
for a few minutes

303
00:26:20.496 --> 00:26:22.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
before you start walking around
on that again.

304
00:26:23.123 --> 00:26:24.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bruno] Will you tell my mum
what happened?

305
00:26:26.710 --> 00:26:28.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think she's going to see it for herself.

306
00:26:30.881 --> 00:26:32.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She'll probably take me to a doctor.

307
00:26:34.551 --> 00:26:35.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Pavel] I don't think so.

308
00:26:36.345 --> 00:26:38.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It could be worse than it looks.

309
00:26:39.056 --> 00:26:40.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It isn't.

310
00:26:40.808 --> 00:26:42.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] How would you know?

311
00:26:42.392 --> 00:26:43.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're not a doctor.

312
00:26:47.981 --> 00:26:48.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, I am.

313
00:26:49.650 --> 00:26:52.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, you're not. You peel potatoes.

314
00:26:54.488 --> 00:26:58.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I practiced as a doctor, before I…

315
00:26:59.368 --> 00:27:00.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before I came here.

316
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:05.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You couldn't have been much good then
if you had to practice.

317
00:27:08.794 --> 00:27:10.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[soft music playing]

318
00:27:14.800 --> 00:27:15.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now…

319
00:27:17.469 --> 00:27:19.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
what are you going to be when you grow up?

320
00:27:20.430 --> 00:27:21.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know.

321
00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:23.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
An explorer.

322
00:27:24.393 --> 00:27:25.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How do you know that?

323
00:27:29.523 --> 00:27:30.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is it nice on the farm?

324
00:27:32.109 --> 00:27:33.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps approaching]

325
00:27:40.409 --> 00:27:42.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bruno. Bruno, what happened to you?

326
00:27:42.995 --> 00:27:46.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I made a swing,
but I fell off it and cut my knee.

327
00:27:46.957 --> 00:27:49.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But Pavel here, he carried me in
and put a bandage on it.

328
00:27:57.801 --> 00:27:59.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Go to your room.
-But Pavel says I--

329
00:27:59.928 --> 00:28:01.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't argue. Go to your room.

330
00:28:09.563 --> 00:28:12.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[object rustling]

331
00:28:12.858 --> 00:28:15.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[potatoes scraping]

332
00:28:30.167 --> 00:28:31.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

333
00:28:38.258 --> 00:28:39.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

334
00:28:52.439 --> 00:28:53.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[waltz music playing]

335
00:28:56.026 --> 00:28:58.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bruno] It's not fair,
you having this view.

336
00:28:58.570 --> 00:29:00.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Gretel] Well, I'm not swapping.

337
00:29:00.656 --> 00:29:01.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bicycle horn dings]

338
00:29:03.242 --> 00:29:04.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[dog barks in distance]

339
00:29:05.661 --> 00:29:06.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think school's here.

340
00:29:09.248 --> 00:29:11.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Liszt] <i>No, I mean, more recent history.</i>

341
00:29:11.750 --> 00:29:13.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you interested in… in current affairs?

342
00:29:13.919 --> 00:29:15.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, very.

343
00:29:15.504 --> 00:29:18.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, you'll be aware of the situation

344
00:29:19.299 --> 00:29:21.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in which our great nation
presently finds itself.

345
00:29:21.843 --> 00:29:24.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. I read newspapers whenever I can,

346
00:29:24.846 --> 00:29:28.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and one of Father's men keeps me up
to date on everything that's happening.

347
00:29:28.308 --> 00:29:32.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good. And you, Bruno?
Have you been reading newspapers?

348
00:29:34.648 --> 00:29:36.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you been reading anything?

349
00:29:37.401 --> 00:29:38.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Books.

350
00:29:39.111 --> 00:29:41.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good. What sort of books?

351
00:29:42.572 --> 00:29:44.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Adventure books, mainly.

352
00:29:44.574 --> 00:29:49.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, knights in shining armor,
exploring strange lands and stuff.

353
00:29:50.080 --> 00:29:52.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And silly princesses
always getting in the way.

354
00:29:52.457 --> 00:29:57.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah. Well, this is why I'm here to help.
You're how old now, Bruno? Eight?

355
00:29:58.171 --> 00:30:00.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Time to get your head out
of those fiction books

356
00:30:00.173 --> 00:30:01.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and start learning about fact.

357
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:05.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Time, I think,
to turn your mind to the real world,

358
00:30:06.054 --> 00:30:08.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I believe
this would be the perfect start.

359
00:30:12.811 --> 00:30:13.770 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[truck engines rumbling]

360
00:30:15.147 --> 00:30:18.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[men singing]

361
00:30:34.541 --> 00:30:36.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[suspenseful music playing]

362
00:31:06.448 --> 00:31:07.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts softly]

363
00:31:18.168 --> 00:31:19.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[birds squawking]

364
00:31:24.841 --> 00:31:25.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno neighs]

365
00:31:44.820 --> 00:31:51.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Die, die! [grunts, neighs]

366
00:31:57.416 --> 00:31:59.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Die. Die!

367
00:32:24.776 --> 00:32:27.070 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[indistinct chatter]
-[music concludes]

368
00:32:47.757 --> 00:32:48.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

369
00:32:53.180 --> 00:32:54.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello.

370
00:32:56.057 --> 00:32:56.933 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

371
00:33:00.479 --> 00:33:01.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm exploring.

372
00:33:07.694 --> 00:33:08.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

373
00:33:09.321 --> 00:33:11.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're… we're building a new hut.

374
00:33:17.412 --> 00:33:19.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bruno] Have you got
lots of friends over there?

375
00:33:21.041 --> 00:33:21.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shmuel] A few.

376
00:33:22.501 --> 00:33:26.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But we fight a lot.
That's why I like being out here.

377
00:33:27.589 --> 00:33:28.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can be on my own.

378
00:33:31.593 --> 00:33:32.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm Bruno.

379
00:33:33.470 --> 00:33:35.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Shmuel.
-[Bruno] Sorry?

380
00:33:35.722 --> 00:33:36.765 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm Shmuel.

381
00:33:38.517 --> 00:33:39.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's your name?

382
00:33:40.101 --> 00:33:42.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never heard of anyone called that before.

383
00:33:42.395 --> 00:33:44.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've never heard of anyone called Bruno.

384
00:33:44.481 --> 00:33:48.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But Shmuel. No one's called Shmuel.

385
00:33:54.491 --> 00:33:56.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I live in the house back there.

386
00:33:59.996 --> 00:34:02.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Have you got any food on you?
-[Bruno] No.

387
00:34:04.251 --> 00:34:05.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you hungry?
-Hmm.

388
00:34:06.211 --> 00:34:08.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[men shouting]

389
00:34:15.053 --> 00:34:16.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How old are you?

390
00:34:17.472 --> 00:34:19.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Eight.
-Me too!

391
00:34:26.106 --> 00:34:29.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not fair, me being stuck
over here on my own,

392
00:34:29.776 --> 00:34:32.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while you're over there
playing with friends all day.

393
00:34:32.487 --> 00:34:35.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Playing?
-Well, that number.

394
00:34:35.991 --> 00:34:38.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Isn't it a part of a game or something?
-It's just my number.

395
00:34:39.411 --> 00:34:41.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Everyone gets given a different number.
-[Bruno] Oh.

396
00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:43.832 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Right. Then what happens?
-[man shouting]

397
00:34:44.040 --> 00:34:45.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[whistle blowing]
-[gasps]

398
00:34:47.210 --> 00:34:48.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have to go back now.

399
00:34:49.337 --> 00:34:50.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Really?
-Yeah.

400
00:34:51.590 --> 00:34:54.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was nice to meet you, Shmuel.

401
00:34:54.509 --> 00:34:56.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you, Bruno.

402
00:34:57.345 --> 00:35:00.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[soldier] Come on! Come back!

403
00:35:07.606 --> 00:35:08.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whispering] Bye.

404
00:35:20.702 --> 00:35:22.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mum, I can't find my football.

405
00:35:22.787 --> 00:35:24.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, it'll be in one of your cupboards,
sweet.

406
00:35:24.914 --> 00:35:26.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It isn't. I've looked.

407
00:35:27.751 --> 00:35:29.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can I have a piece of chocolate?

408
00:35:29.919 --> 00:35:32.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm. A piece. Yes.

409
00:35:39.095 --> 00:35:41.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bruno? Have you looked in the cellar?

410
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:46.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-The cellar?
-For your football.

411
00:35:47.062 --> 00:35:47.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

412
00:36:00.617 --> 00:36:02.077 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[tense music playing]

413
00:36:25.225 --> 00:36:26.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[object clatters]
-[Bruno] Damn.

414
00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:28.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[switch clicks]

415
00:36:53.294 --> 00:36:54.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Gretel, I've just seen all your…

416
00:36:55.630 --> 00:36:56.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All my what?

417
00:36:57.841 --> 00:37:01.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All your dolls down in the cellar.

418
00:37:02.095 --> 00:37:07.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dolls are for little girls.
It's not right to play with silly toys

419
00:37:08.059 --> 00:37:11.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
while people are away risking
their lives for the Fatherland.

420
00:37:19.446 --> 00:37:21.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[whistle blows]

421
00:37:28.288 --> 00:37:29.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

422
00:37:46.264 --> 00:37:48.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[electricity crackles]

423
00:37:52.687 --> 00:37:56.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-"My people's density is my density."
-Destiny.

424
00:37:59.235 --> 00:38:02.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"Its struggles and its sorrows,
its joys and its miseries are mine."

425
00:38:02.989 --> 00:38:06.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"I must work and create
for the resurrection of my Fatherland."

426
00:38:06.743 --> 00:38:09.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"The history of my people
is great and glorious."

427
00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:10.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And it's twelve o'clock.

428
00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:14.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry?

429
00:38:16.211 --> 00:38:17.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Isn't that when we finish?

430
00:38:18.296 --> 00:38:20.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The termination of the lesson
is for the tutor

431
00:38:20.632 --> 00:38:23.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to decide, Bruno, not the pupil.
Now, will you please continue.

432
00:38:39.651 --> 00:38:40.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, Bruno, there you are.

433
00:38:41.986 --> 00:38:44.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just going into town for an hour.

434
00:38:45.031 --> 00:38:45.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you want to come?

435
00:38:48.243 --> 00:38:50.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You be careful on that thing.

436
00:38:50.745 --> 00:38:52.330 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Thank you.
-[car door closes]

437
00:38:54.123 --> 00:38:55.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[car door shuts]
-[car engine revving]

438
00:39:10.265 --> 00:39:11.349 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno]<i> Can I ask you something?</i>

439
00:39:12.517 --> 00:39:14.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why do you people wear pajamas all day?

440
00:39:15.895 --> 00:39:17.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're not pajamas.

441
00:39:18.022 --> 00:39:19.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, those.

442
00:39:20.191 --> 00:39:22.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have to.
They took all our other clothes away.

443
00:39:23.152 --> 00:39:24.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Bruno] Who did?
-The soldiers.

444
00:39:25.154 --> 00:39:26.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] The soldiers? Why?

445
00:39:29.742 --> 00:39:32.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't like soldiers. Do you?

446
00:39:33.538 --> 00:39:36.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[clicks tongue] I do, quite.
My dad's a soldier.

447
00:39:37.208 --> 00:39:39.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But not the sort that takes
people's clothes away for no reason.

448
00:39:40.628 --> 00:39:41.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What sort, then?

449
00:39:44.048 --> 00:39:46.342 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] Well, he's the important sort.

450
00:39:46.843 --> 00:39:49.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's in charge of making
everything better for everyone.

451
00:39:52.265 --> 00:39:53.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, is your dad a farmer?

452
00:39:55.059 --> 00:39:56.227 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, he's a watchmaker.

453
00:39:57.854 --> 00:40:01.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or was.
Most of the time now, he just mends boots.

454
00:40:05.069 --> 00:40:07.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's funny how grown-ups
can't make their minds up

455
00:40:07.280 --> 00:40:08.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
about what they want to do.

456
00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:12.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's like Pavel.
Do you know him? Lives over there.

457
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:18.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He used to be a doctor,
but gave it all up to peel potatoes.

458
00:40:28.593 --> 00:40:30.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] <i>Can I ask you another question?</i>

459
00:40:30.637 --> 00:40:32.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you burn in those chimneys?

460
00:40:32.931 --> 00:40:34.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I saw them going the other day.

461
00:40:34.724 --> 00:40:36.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is it just lots of hay and stuff?

462
00:40:36.684 --> 00:40:39.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know.
We're not allowed over there.

463
00:40:39.812 --> 00:40:41.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mama says it's old clothes.

464
00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:44.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, whatever it is, it smells horrid.

465
00:40:44.984 --> 00:40:45.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles softly]

466
00:40:47.528 --> 00:40:50.031 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] I wish
you'd remembered the chocolate.

467
00:40:50.323 --> 00:40:51.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, I'm sorry.

468
00:40:52.116 --> 00:40:54.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know. Perhaps you can come
and have supper with us sometime.

469
00:40:55.286 --> 00:40:57.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can't, can I? Because of this.

470
00:40:58.539 --> 00:41:01.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But that's to stop
the animals getting out, isn't it?

471
00:41:01.209 --> 00:41:04.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Animals?
No, it's to stop people getting out.

472
00:41:04.879 --> 00:41:06.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you not allowed out?

473
00:41:07.882 --> 00:41:09.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why? What have you done?

474
00:41:10.677 --> 00:41:11.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm a Jew.

475
00:41:24.691 --> 00:41:26.067 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I should go now.

476
00:41:31.489 --> 00:41:32.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Will you be here tomorrow?

477
00:41:33.032 --> 00:41:35.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll try. Goodbye, then!

478
00:41:36.160 --> 00:41:37.078 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bye.

479
00:41:38.037 --> 00:41:40.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[men singing]
-[door knocks]

480
00:41:41.374 --> 00:41:42.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Little present, sweetheart.

481
00:41:47.005 --> 00:41:48.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, Mummy.

482
00:41:56.514 --> 00:41:59.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Have you seen Bruno?
-Outside on his swing, I think.

483
00:42:13.531 --> 00:42:16.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ralf] Yes, Thursday's perfect.
I'll have a car come to collect you both.

484
00:42:17.243 --> 00:42:18.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are Grandma and Grandpa coming?

485
00:42:19.704 --> 00:42:20.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] Mm-hmm.

486
00:42:20.955 --> 00:42:23.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, did you smell that horrible smell
the other day?

487
00:42:24.333 --> 00:42:25.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Coming from the chimneys.

488
00:42:25.793 --> 00:42:27.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] What sort of ill?

489
00:42:28.880 --> 00:42:30.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The day I fell off the swing.

490
00:42:31.841 --> 00:42:33.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did you smell it, Mum?

491
00:42:33.509 --> 00:42:35.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Ralf] Father.
-Mum.

492
00:42:35.553 --> 00:42:37.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] I… [sighs]

493
00:42:37.847 --> 00:42:39.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me speak to her.

494
00:42:39.682 --> 00:42:41.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] Yes, she is. I can hear her.

495
00:42:42.935 --> 00:42:44.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

496
00:42:45.188 --> 00:42:47.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. We look forward to it. Goodbye.

497
00:42:48.441 --> 00:42:49.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[receiver clatters]

498
00:42:50.693 --> 00:42:51.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

499
00:42:53.529 --> 00:42:55.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Is Grandma not coming?
-No.

500
00:42:56.074 --> 00:42:59.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's poorly, apparently,
but Grandpa's coming.

501
00:43:01.746 --> 00:43:03.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Did you smell it, Dad?
-What?

502
00:43:03.873 --> 00:43:05.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bruno] That horrid smell
from the chimneys.

503
00:43:06.501 --> 00:43:07.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it?

504
00:43:10.004 --> 00:43:13.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[smacks lips] I think
they just burn rubbish there sometimes.

505
00:43:13.591 --> 00:43:14.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look.

506
00:43:14.967 --> 00:43:15.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

507
00:43:17.929 --> 00:43:19.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Hey!
-[Elsa] Gretel.

508
00:43:20.264 --> 00:43:21.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

509
00:43:21.849 --> 00:43:23.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, that's not fair!

510
00:43:23.309 --> 00:43:24.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Gretel.
-What?

511
00:43:25.478 --> 00:43:26.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's only a game.

512
00:43:32.485 --> 00:43:34.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ralf, this tutor you brought in,

513
00:43:35.113 --> 00:43:37.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
does he usually teach children
as young as Gretel and Bruno?

514
00:43:39.492 --> 00:43:40.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I believe so. Why?

515
00:43:41.119 --> 00:43:42.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, do we know
what he's teaching them?

516
00:43:42.954 --> 00:43:44.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Gretel seems to have become so--

517
00:43:45.123 --> 00:43:47.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're being taught
what all children are being taught

518
00:43:47.291 --> 00:43:49.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
at the moment.
They mustn't get left behind.

519
00:43:50.753 --> 00:43:51.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on.

520
00:43:52.296 --> 00:43:53.172 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[kisses]

521
00:43:54.132 --> 00:43:55.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's get to bed.

522
00:44:06.435 --> 00:44:09.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"The Jew slandered us
and incited our enemies."

523
00:44:09.147 --> 00:44:13.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"The Jew corrupted us through bad books.
He mocked our literature and our music."

524
00:44:13.985 --> 00:44:16.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"Everywhere,
his influence was destructive,

525
00:44:16.487 --> 00:44:20.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the eventual result of which
was our nation's collapse, and then--"

526
00:44:20.241 --> 00:44:21.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, Bruno.

527
00:44:21.868 --> 00:44:23.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't understand.

528
00:44:24.203 --> 00:44:26.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A nation's collapse
is all down to this one man?

529
00:44:27.290 --> 00:44:30.084 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Jew here means the entire Jewish race.

530
00:44:30.835 --> 00:44:32.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If it had been just one man,

531
00:44:32.920 --> 00:44:35.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure something
would've been done about him.

532
00:44:37.633 --> 00:44:40.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There is such a thing
as a nice Jew though, isn't there?

533
00:44:40.845 --> 00:44:44.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think, Bruno,
if you ever found a nice Jew,

534
00:44:45.892 --> 00:44:48.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you would be the best explorer
in the world.

535
00:44:50.396 --> 00:44:52.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[somber music playing]

536
00:44:53.107 --> 00:44:54.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Liszt] Continue, Gretel.

537
00:44:56.652 --> 00:44:59.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Gretel] "The aim of the Jew
is to become the ruler of humanity."

538
00:44:59.655 --> 00:45:02.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>"The Jew is not creative,</i>
<i>but destructive."</i>

539
00:45:02.575 --> 00:45:04.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"He is the enemy of culture."

540
00:45:05.161 --> 00:45:07.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"Thousands of Germans
have been made poor by the Jew."

541
00:45:10.708 --> 00:45:11.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music fades]

542
00:45:12.293 --> 00:45:17.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[jet engine rumbling]

543
00:45:21.761 --> 00:45:22.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Maria] Master Bruno.

544
00:45:24.305 --> 00:45:26.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What are you doing?
You've just had your lunch, haven't you?

545
00:45:27.850 --> 00:45:31.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was going for a walk,
and I thought I might get peckish.

546
00:45:31.812 --> 00:45:34.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But don't make a mess of your satchel.
Bring it here.

547
00:45:34.523 --> 00:45:35.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll wrap it properly for you.

548
00:45:37.026 --> 00:45:39.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Bruno] No. It's none of your business.
-[footsteps approaching]

549
00:45:39.278 --> 00:45:40.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bruno, what is it?

550
00:45:41.948 --> 00:45:43.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing with your satchel?

551
00:45:44.325 --> 00:45:46.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Herr Liszt gave us some books.

552
00:45:46.994 --> 00:45:48.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm going out on the swing to read.

553
00:45:50.498 --> 00:45:51.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me see.

554
00:45:51.916 --> 00:45:53.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What?
-[Elsa] The books.

555
00:45:54.502 --> 00:45:55.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

556
00:45:55.544 --> 00:45:57.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bruno, I just want to see what books
Herr Liszt has given you.

557
00:46:00.716 --> 00:46:02.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I told a lie.
-What?

558
00:46:03.886 --> 00:46:05.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've just got…

559
00:46:07.974 --> 00:46:09.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
adventure books.

560
00:46:14.939 --> 00:46:15.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

561
00:46:17.108 --> 00:46:20.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[kisses] Go on.
Off you go, then. [chuckles]

562
00:46:23.781 --> 00:46:25.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, Maria, there's two extra
for supper tonight.

563
00:46:25.950 --> 00:46:27.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, the <i>Kommandant's</i> father will be here,

564
00:46:27.660 --> 00:46:29.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I believe
Lieutenant Kotler is joining us.

565
00:46:37.837 --> 00:46:41.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chomping]

566
00:46:52.601 --> 00:46:53.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] Here.

567
00:46:59.775 --> 00:47:02.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shmuel grunting, panting]

568
00:47:05.239 --> 00:47:06.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] What's the matter?

569
00:47:07.950 --> 00:47:08.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunts]

570
00:47:09.368 --> 00:47:10.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't throw it back.

571
00:47:11.245 --> 00:47:12.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? Why not?

572
00:47:13.789 --> 00:47:14.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's dangerous.

573
00:47:14.874 --> 00:47:17.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dangerous? It's just a ball. Come on.

574
00:47:20.296 --> 00:47:21.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[tense music playing]

575
00:47:21.839 --> 00:47:22.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you not like playing?

576
00:47:23.215 --> 00:47:24.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

577
00:47:27.219 --> 00:47:28.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just not ball games?

578
00:47:29.138 --> 00:47:30.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not here.

579
00:47:35.227 --> 00:47:36.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me how the number game works.

580
00:47:37.104 --> 00:47:40.358 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you, it's not a game.
We just all have numbers.

581
00:47:40.483 --> 00:47:41.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[whistle blowing]
-[gasps]

582
00:47:41.734 --> 00:47:43.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man shouting]

583
00:47:46.238 --> 00:47:48.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[soldier] Shmuel!
-Shmuel!

584
00:48:02.963 --> 00:48:05.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bruno! What are you doing?

585
00:48:06.842 --> 00:48:09.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My ball went over.
I was just getting it back.

586
00:48:15.267 --> 00:48:16.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

587
00:48:19.730 --> 00:48:21.690 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They smell even worse
when they burn, don't they?

588
00:48:22.650 --> 00:48:23.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

589
00:48:40.626 --> 00:48:41.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But surely you…

590
00:48:51.679 --> 00:48:53.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

591
00:48:56.600 --> 00:49:00.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[exhales] Elsa, I was sworn to secrecy.

592
00:49:00.855 --> 00:49:02.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-From your own wife.
-[Ralf] Yes.

593
00:49:06.902 --> 00:49:11.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I took an oath upon my life.
Do you understand?

594
00:49:13.242 --> 00:49:15.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Elsa, you believe in this, too.

595
00:49:16.829 --> 00:49:21.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You want this country to be strong--
-No, Ralf, no! No, not that!

596
00:49:26.422 --> 00:49:28.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How can you--

597
00:49:28.090 --> 00:49:29.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Because I'm a soldier.
-[Elsa] How can you?

598
00:49:29.884 --> 00:49:32.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Soldiers fight wars.
-That isn't war!

599
00:49:32.595 --> 00:49:35.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a part of it!
It's a vital part of it!

600
00:49:36.307 --> 00:49:39.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[sobs]
-The Fatherland we all desire,

601
00:49:39.435 --> 00:49:40.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
all of us, you included,

602
00:49:40.936 --> 00:49:43.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
cannot be achieved
without work such as this!

603
00:49:46.484 --> 00:49:49.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Elsa. Elsa.
-Get away from me!

604
00:49:50.196 --> 00:49:54.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Get away from me! [sobs]

605
00:49:56.160 --> 00:49:57.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grandpa's here.

606
00:49:57.286 --> 00:49:59.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I don't believe this.
-[Bruno] Grandpa's here.

607
00:50:03.626 --> 00:50:04.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll be through in a moment.

608
00:50:15.763 --> 00:50:17.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who told you about this?

609
00:50:49.588 --> 00:50:50.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How's Grandma?

610
00:50:51.632 --> 00:50:54.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh. She's… she's a bit
under the weather, I'm afraid.

611
00:50:54.176 --> 00:50:55.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a shame, she…

612
00:50:55.469 --> 00:50:57.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
she was so much looking
forward to seeing you.

613
00:50:58.305 --> 00:51:01.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Perhaps next time, if she feels up to it.
-[Matthias] Oh, absolutely.

614
00:51:08.732 --> 00:51:09.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know, Ralf,

615
00:51:11.151 --> 00:51:13.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
your mother really is sick.

616
00:51:14.363 --> 00:51:16.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's been talking
about this visit for weeks.

617
00:51:16.699 --> 00:51:18.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe that's what's made her sick.

618
00:51:25.916 --> 00:51:29.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Matthias] So, your father tells me
that you've got a tutor.

619
00:51:29.920 --> 00:51:31.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. He's nice.

620
00:51:32.631 --> 00:51:34.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bruno] But he won't let us read
any adventure books.

621
00:51:35.968 --> 00:51:37.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All we do is boring, old history.

622
00:51:38.137 --> 00:51:40.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Matthias chuckles]
Let me tell you something, young man.

623
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:44.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it wasn't for history, we wouldn't all
be sitting around this table.

624
00:51:45.436 --> 00:51:51.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The work your father is doing here,
history in the making.

625
00:52:01.493 --> 00:52:05.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I was your age,
history was my favorite subject by miles,

626
00:52:05.497 --> 00:52:07.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which obviously
didn't please my father.

627
00:52:07.499 --> 00:52:08.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm? Why not?

628
00:52:09.293 --> 00:52:12.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, he was a professor
of literature at the university.

629
00:52:12.338 --> 00:52:15.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? Does he still teach?

630
00:52:18.677 --> 00:52:22.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I don't really know.
-You don't… you don't know?

631
00:52:25.225 --> 00:52:30.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're not in touch, my father and I.
He, um, left the country some time ago.

632
00:52:32.524 --> 00:52:33.400 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? When?

633
00:52:36.028 --> 00:52:39.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[smacks lips]
About four years ago, Herr <i>Kommandant.</i>

634
00:52:43.160 --> 00:52:44.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But surely, he can't be very old.

635
00:52:44.870 --> 00:52:47.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What is he,
still in his forties, late forties?

636
00:52:48.374 --> 00:52:49.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did he go?

637
00:52:57.341 --> 00:52:59.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[tense music playing]
-[Ralf] Lieutenant Kotler.

638
00:53:01.136 --> 00:53:04.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your father, the professor of literature,
where did he go?

639
00:53:10.562 --> 00:53:12.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it was Switzerland,
Herr <i>Kommandant.</i>

640
00:53:14.775 --> 00:53:17.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ralf] How strange that he should choose
to leave the Fatherland

641
00:53:17.319 --> 00:53:18.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
at the very moment it needed him most.

642
00:53:18.987 --> 00:53:20.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just when we're all required
to play our part

643
00:53:20.614 --> 00:53:22.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the national revival. More wine!

644
00:53:25.577 --> 00:53:27.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What reason did he give?
Was he tubercular?

645
00:53:28.330 --> 00:53:29.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Herr<i> Kommandant</i>?

646
00:53:31.291 --> 00:53:33.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did he go there to take the air?

647
00:53:35.504 --> 00:53:38.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid, I really don't know,
Herr<i> Kommandant</i>. You'd have to ask him.

648
00:53:39.425 --> 00:53:41.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ralf] Well, that would be rather
difficult, wouldn't it,

649
00:53:42.261 --> 00:53:44.138 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with him being in Switzerland? [scoffs]

650
00:53:45.139 --> 00:53:46.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Come on!
-[table thuds]

651
00:53:47.641 --> 00:53:48.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's the matter with you tonight?

652
00:53:58.527 --> 00:54:00.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, perhaps that was it.

653
00:54:01.780 --> 00:54:03.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps he was ill.

654
00:54:05.033 --> 00:54:07.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Unless, of course, he had disagreements.

655
00:54:09.955 --> 00:54:11.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I mean, with government policy.

656
00:54:12.291 --> 00:54:15.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One hears of such men.
Disturbed, most of them.

657
00:54:16.795 --> 00:54:18.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or just plain cowards.

658
00:54:18.338 --> 00:54:21.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Even so, all of them traitors.
-[Ralf] Absolutely right.

659
00:54:22.176 --> 00:54:26.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Presumably, if that was the case
with your father,

660
00:54:26.346 --> 00:54:30.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you will have informed
your superiors, as is your duty.

661
00:54:32.394 --> 00:54:34.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Kotler.

662
00:54:35.022 --> 00:54:37.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[whimpers]
-You cretin Jew!

663
00:54:37.316 --> 00:54:38.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Filth!

664
00:54:39.276 --> 00:54:45.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Pavel groaning]
-[Kurt grunting]

665
00:54:49.995 --> 00:54:50.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ralf!

666
00:54:56.168 --> 00:54:57.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kurt] Jew!

667
00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.005 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] <i>Dad just sat there.</i>

668
00:55:00.380 --> 00:55:03.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What did you expect him to do?
The Jew deserved it.

669
00:55:03.967 --> 00:55:05.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

670
00:55:13.268 --> 00:55:16.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can I ask you something…
[sniffles] …about the farm?

671
00:55:17.272 --> 00:55:20.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, Bruno, you don't still think
it's a farm, do you?

672
00:55:39.002 --> 00:55:40.087 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a camp.

673
00:55:41.046 --> 00:55:45.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, it's called a work camp.
For Jews, obviously.

674
00:55:47.010 --> 00:55:51.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just Jews?
Because they're the best workers?

675
00:55:52.558 --> 00:55:54.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're not in there
because they're good, silly.

676
00:55:54.726 --> 00:55:58.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're no good at anything.
They're in there because they're evil.

677
00:55:58.230 --> 00:55:59.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-They're the enemy.
-The enemy?

678
00:56:00.691 --> 00:56:03.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-But I thought we were fighting--
-They're evil, Bruno.

679
00:56:03.193 --> 00:56:04.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Evil, dangerous vermin.

680
00:56:05.696 --> 00:56:07.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're the reason we lost the Great War.

681
00:56:08.490 --> 00:56:11.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Haven't you been listening to anything
Herr Liszt has been telling us?

682
00:56:12.578 --> 00:56:13.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Not really.

683
00:56:15.914 --> 00:56:16.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

684
00:56:16.957 --> 00:56:20.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dad's not horrible, is he?
He's a good man.

685
00:56:20.210 --> 00:56:21.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course, he is.

686
00:56:22.379 --> 00:56:24.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But he's in charge of a horrible place.

687
00:56:25.173 --> 00:56:26.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's only horrible for them, Bruno.

688
00:56:27.342 --> 00:56:29.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We should be proud of Dad,
now more than ever before.

689
00:56:30.095 --> 00:56:31.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's making the country great again.

690
00:56:33.098 --> 00:56:35.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[floor scrubbing]
-[tense music playing]

691
00:56:43.317 --> 00:56:45.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

692
00:56:59.875 --> 00:57:01.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[tense music playing]

693
00:57:17.267 --> 00:57:18.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs softly]

694
00:57:24.942 --> 00:57:27.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Elsa] <i>Like you say,</i>
<i>they're a bit strange. A bit…</i>

695
00:57:28.278 --> 00:57:30.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-Well, they're different.</i>
<i>-</i>[Gretel]<i> They're the enemy, Bruno.</i>

696
00:57:31.490 --> 00:57:32.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Evil, dangerous vermin.</i>

697
00:57:33.283 --> 00:57:36.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ralf] <i>Well, you see,</i>
<i>they're not really people at all.</i>

698
00:57:41.792 --> 00:57:43.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music fades]

699
00:57:46.254 --> 00:57:48.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[soft music playing]

700
00:57:59.893 --> 00:58:02.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[chuckles softly] What are you doing here?

701
00:58:02.980 --> 00:58:07.150 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They wanted someone
with tiny fingers to clean all these.

702
00:58:19.913 --> 00:58:22.124 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're not supposed to be friends,
you and me.

703
00:58:23.125 --> 00:58:25.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're meant to be enemies.
Did you know that?

704
00:58:33.176 --> 00:58:34.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you want some?

705
00:58:45.313 --> 00:58:47.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What's your dad like?
-What's he like?

706
00:58:48.400 --> 00:58:49.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is he a good man?

707
00:58:53.071 --> 00:58:54.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You've never thought he wasn't?

708
00:58:57.993 --> 00:58:59.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you're proud of him?

709
00:59:01.329 --> 00:59:02.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Aren't you proud of yours?

710
00:59:07.753 --> 00:59:09.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Is it really horrible in the camp?
-[door opens]

711
00:59:10.005 --> 00:59:10.881 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Shmuel gasps]

712
00:59:11.006 --> 00:59:12.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How dare you talk to people in the house?

713
00:59:13.216 --> 00:59:15.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How dare you?

714
00:59:17.721 --> 00:59:19.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Are you eating?
-[Shmuel whimpers softly]

715
00:59:21.850 --> 00:59:23.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you been stealing food?

716
00:59:27.856 --> 00:59:29.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Answer me!
-[gasps] No, sir.

717
00:59:30.734 --> 00:59:31.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He gave it to me.

718
00:59:32.986 --> 00:59:33.904 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's my friend.

719
00:59:36.698 --> 00:59:37.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

720
00:59:38.158 --> 00:59:39.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[tense music playing]

721
00:59:40.619 --> 00:59:41.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Little man…

722
00:59:43.830 --> 00:59:44.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
do you know this Jew?

723
00:59:46.249 --> 00:59:47.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you know this Jew?

724
00:59:47.876 --> 00:59:50.670 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I just walked in
and he was helping himself.

725
00:59:51.088 --> 00:59:53.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've never seen him before in my life.

726
01:00:02.766 --> 01:00:05.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You, finish cleaning the glasses.

727
01:00:06.728 --> 01:00:10.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I come back, we'll have a little chat
about what happens to rats who steal.

728
01:00:11.483 --> 01:00:12.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come away.

729
01:00:30.377 --> 01:00:31.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno grunts]

730
01:00:34.589 --> 01:00:35.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sniffles]

731
01:00:39.636 --> 01:00:40.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sniffles]

732
01:01:11.126 --> 01:01:13.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

733
01:01:13.962 --> 01:01:15.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[pants]

734
01:01:16.798 --> 01:01:19.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[dramatic music playing]

735
01:01:24.556 --> 01:01:26.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[insects chirping]

736
01:01:31.688 --> 01:01:34.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cars approaching]

737
01:01:51.875 --> 01:01:53.035 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music fades]

738
01:01:53.110 --> 01:01:55.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[narrator on projector]
<i>New arrivals here are happy to discover</i>

739
01:01:55.310 --> 01:01:57.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[instrumental music playing]
<i>-that life in the camp is not all work.</i>

740
01:01:57.797 --> 01:02:00.717 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And that there's ample opportunity</i>
<i>for leisure also.</i>

741
01:02:01.176 --> 01:02:03.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>At the end of their day</i>
<i>at the ironmongery,</i>

742
01:02:03.637 --> 01:02:05.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>or the build or boot factory,</i>

743
01:02:05.138 --> 01:02:07.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the workers can enjoy</i>
<i>the many forms of pastime</i>

744
01:02:07.641 --> 01:02:09.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>that the camp has to offer.</i>

745
01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:12.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Organized sport is very popular.</i>

746
01:02:13.146 --> 01:02:15.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Those that don't play</i>
<i>certainly enjoy watching.</i>

747
01:02:18.401 --> 01:02:21.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>At the end of the working day,</i>
<i>the centrally-located café</i>

748
01:02:21.363 --> 01:02:23.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>is the ideal place</i>
<i>for friends and families</i>

749
01:02:23.406 --> 01:02:26.243 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to join together</i>
<i>for a hearty and nutritious meal.</i>

750
01:02:27.744 --> 01:02:29.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The children in particular</i>
<i>enjoy the pastries</i>

751
01:02:29.871 --> 01:02:31.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and cakes on offer.</i>

752
01:02:31.331 --> 01:02:32.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs]

753
01:02:37.337 --> 01:02:39.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[narrator on projector] <i>In the evenings,</i>
<i>the occasional music concerts,</i>

754
01:02:39.881 --> 01:02:42.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>either by visiting orchestras</i>
<i>or indeed, by talented musicians</i>

755
01:02:43.051 --> 01:02:46.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>from within the camp itself,</i>
<i>are always well-attended.</i>

756
01:02:48.181 --> 01:02:50.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Other recreations include</i>
<i>reading in the library,</i>

757
01:02:50.600 --> 01:02:56.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>pottery, cookery, art, and horticulture</i>
<i>for adult and child alike.</i>

758
01:02:56.731 --> 01:03:00.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Almost any activity one could wish for</i>
<i>is available within the camp.</i>

759
01:03:02.445 --> 01:03:04.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

760
01:03:05.949 --> 01:03:07.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

761
01:03:18.295 --> 01:03:20.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Matthias] Bravo. Excellent.
-[Ralf] Thank you.

762
01:03:20.630 --> 01:03:22.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Matthias] Excellent.
-[Ralf] Thank you.

763
01:03:22.757 --> 01:03:25.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

764
01:03:26.094 --> 01:03:27.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[instrumental music playing]

765
01:03:29.931 --> 01:03:31.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct chatter]

766
01:04:07.010 --> 01:04:08.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Goodbye, little man.

767
01:04:55.642 --> 01:04:57.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shmuel! Shmuel!

768
01:05:01.606 --> 01:05:03.191 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music concludes]

769
01:05:14.536 --> 01:05:19.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't understand.
I saw a film about the camp.

770
01:05:20.625 --> 01:05:22.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And it looked so nice.

771
01:05:29.926 --> 01:05:31.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know why I did it.

772
01:05:32.303 --> 01:05:34.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Gretel and everyone
were saying all these things,

773
01:05:35.181 --> 01:05:36.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and that soldier's so scary.

774
01:05:42.522 --> 01:05:46.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Been coming here for days,
but you were never here.

775
01:05:46.276 --> 01:05:48.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought maybe…

776
01:05:50.071 --> 01:05:51.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
we weren't friends anymore.

777
01:05:59.581 --> 01:06:03.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shmuel, I'm really sorry for what I did.
We are still friends, aren't we?

778
01:06:23.855 --> 01:06:25.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[telephone ringing]

779
01:06:29.486 --> 01:06:31.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[telephone ringing]
-[receiver clattering]

780
01:06:35.575 --> 01:06:36.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Gretel] Where's Kurt these days?

781
01:06:37.535 --> 01:06:38.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't seen him for ages.

782
01:06:40.580 --> 01:06:41.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who's Kurt?

783
01:06:42.790 --> 01:06:44.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Kotler.

784
01:06:45.919 --> 01:06:47.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's been moved to the front.

785
01:06:48.296 --> 01:06:51.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was felt that his youth and enthusiasm
would be put to better use there.

786
01:06:52.008 --> 01:06:53.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Herr <i>Kommandant,</i> telephone.

787
01:06:55.178 --> 01:06:57.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In actual facts, Gretel, he was sent there

788
01:06:57.680 --> 01:06:59.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because he failed to inform
the authorities

789
01:06:59.599 --> 01:07:01.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of his father's
lack of loyalty to the party.

790
01:07:02.060 --> 01:07:04.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which was his duty, I might add.

791
01:07:04.145 --> 01:07:06.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Which was his bad luck.
-Bad luck?

792
01:07:06.314 --> 01:07:10.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, bad luck that it was his father
who was disloyal, and not his mother.

793
01:07:10.318 --> 01:07:13.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One presumably
doesn't have to report one's mother.

794
01:07:18.660 --> 01:07:20.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Ralf] What?
-When will Pavel be back?

795
01:07:23.790 --> 01:07:24.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mum?

796
01:07:25.208 --> 01:07:26.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never, stupid.

797
01:07:31.214 --> 01:07:32.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's Father. They've been bombed.

798
01:07:38.972 --> 01:07:39.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grandmother's dead.

799
01:07:44.060 --> 01:07:46.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[melancholic music playing]

800
01:07:50.733 --> 01:07:51.693 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bell tolls]

801
01:07:56.281 --> 01:07:57.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bell tolls]

802
01:08:23.141 --> 01:08:24.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bell tolls]

803
01:08:26.227 --> 01:08:28.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
"…The victory
which you have obtained for us,

804
01:08:28.646 --> 01:08:30.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and for all who sleep in him,

805
01:08:31.983 --> 01:08:34.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who are still in the body
in everlasting fellowship

806
01:08:34.652 --> 01:08:36.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
with all that wait for thee on earth,

807
01:08:36.904 --> 01:08:39.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and with all
that are around thee in heaven,

808
01:08:39.699 --> 01:08:42.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in union with Him
who is the resurrection and the life,

809
01:08:42.744 --> 01:08:45.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who liveth and reigneth
with thee and the Holy Ghost,

810
01:08:45.872 --> 01:08:48.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
ever one God, world without end. Amen."

811
01:08:48.708 --> 01:08:51.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
He can't have that on there.
She wouldn't have wanted it.

812
01:08:53.880 --> 01:08:55.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He does.

813
01:09:06.434 --> 01:09:07.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

814
01:09:21.908 --> 01:09:22.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sobs softly]

815
01:09:22.909 --> 01:09:24.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[priest] "All mighty God,
who by the death of…"

816
01:09:24.692 --> 01:09:26.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Bruno] <i>Have you ever been to a funeral?</i>

817
01:09:26.496 --> 01:09:27.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music fades]

818
01:09:28.081 --> 01:09:31.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My grandma and grandpa
both died just after we got here,

819
01:09:31.376 --> 01:09:33.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but there weren't any funerals.

820
01:09:36.214 --> 01:09:38.633 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That one there to there.

821
01:09:41.678 --> 01:09:43.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They both died at the same time?

822
01:09:44.514 --> 01:09:45.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What of?

823
01:09:47.100 --> 01:09:48.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know.

824
01:09:48.351 --> 01:09:50.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Papa said they must have caught something
on the way here.

825
01:09:52.230 --> 01:09:54.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They had to go to a hospital
as soon as we arrived.

826
01:09:55.566 --> 01:09:56.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We didn't see them again.

827
01:10:01.280 --> 01:10:02.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs] This is fun.

828
01:10:03.574 --> 01:10:06.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hmm. Wish we could do something
a bit more exciting, though.

829
01:10:11.165 --> 01:10:13.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[smacks lips] Ah. That one there to there.

830
01:10:14.585 --> 01:10:15.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This one?

831
01:10:17.296 --> 01:10:18.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-This one?
-No, that one.

832
01:10:19.549 --> 01:10:22.719 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-This one to here?
-No, there!

833
01:10:22.927 --> 01:10:24.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[chuckles] To here?
-[chuckles] No!

834
01:10:24.929 --> 01:10:26.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Bruno] Here?
-No!

835
01:10:26.472 --> 01:10:29.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[soft tender music playing]
-[both chuckle]

836
01:10:34.564 --> 01:10:36.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't want you to go away again.

837
01:10:37.817 --> 01:10:39.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Neither do I.

838
01:11:06.971 --> 01:11:08.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music fades]

839
01:11:08.264 --> 01:11:10.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Ralf] <i>You can't behave like this!</i>

840
01:11:10.892 --> 01:11:12.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Elsa] You're questioning my behavior?

841
01:11:12.894 --> 01:11:15.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Ralf] It can't continue!
-[Elsa] I know.

842
01:11:16.147 --> 01:11:17.064 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[door opens]

843
01:11:17.148 --> 01:11:19.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Elsa] I can't stay here
and be a part of this.

844
01:11:20.735 --> 01:11:22.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Ralf] Don't you think
there will be questions?

845
01:11:22.487 --> 01:11:24.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Elsa] Questions?
-[Ralf] Well, what does it say

846
01:11:24.197 --> 01:11:28.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
about my ability to carry out my work
if I cannot control my own family?

847
01:11:29.035 --> 01:11:30.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Elsa] Work? Is that what you call it?
-[Ralf] I do.

848
01:11:31.120 --> 01:11:33.289 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Ralf] Just ignore it.
-[Elsa] Right. Just ignore it.

849
01:11:33.372 --> 01:11:37.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Elsa] Ignore it. Ignore the fact
that the man I married is a monster!

850
01:11:37.794 --> 01:11:39.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Even your own mother couldn't love you.

851
01:11:50.181 --> 01:11:51.057 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Are you happy here?

852
01:11:53.476 --> 01:11:55.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. Very.

853
01:11:58.356 --> 01:11:59.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you, Gretel?

854
01:12:01.776 --> 01:12:05.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, I was, but I do miss home.

855
01:12:06.030 --> 01:12:09.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I miss my friends.
-Yes, I'm sure.

856
01:12:09.742 --> 01:12:13.329 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And you too, Bruno.
You must miss those friends of yours, hmm?

857
01:12:13.996 --> 01:12:16.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. Not anymore, really.

858
01:12:28.511 --> 01:12:30.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose the real question

859
01:12:31.639 --> 01:12:34.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
is if the opportunity arose,

860
01:12:35.309 --> 01:12:37.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
would you prefer to live somewhere else?

861
01:12:37.812 --> 01:12:38.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Gretel] Back home?

862
01:12:39.772 --> 01:12:43.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. Not Berlin. Not yet.
Somewhere safe. Say, uh,

863
01:12:45.027 --> 01:12:47.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Aunt Lottie's in Heidelberg,
for example.

864
01:12:48.406 --> 01:12:50.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All of us? You as well?

865
01:12:51.701 --> 01:12:54.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. That won't be possible
just yet, I'm afraid.

866
01:12:55.037 --> 01:12:56.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I must stay and complete my work here.

867
01:13:00.042 --> 01:13:03.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] See, at the moment,
your mother is finding it…

868
01:13:06.132 --> 01:13:07.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She just feels, right now,

869
01:13:08.217 --> 01:13:11.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you need to spend some time elsewhere.
Would you like that?

870
01:13:22.231 --> 01:13:23.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm afraid, Bruno,

871
01:13:24.358 --> 01:13:27.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in life, we often have to do things
we don't want to do.

872
01:13:27.862 --> 01:13:30.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The important thing
is your mother does not feel

873
01:13:30.323 --> 01:13:33.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that this is an appropriate place for you
to be spending your childhood.

874
01:13:33.367 --> 01:13:36.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And the more I think about it, the more
I realize she's very probably right.

875
01:13:36.954 --> 01:13:38.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-But, Dad--
-No!

876
01:13:45.546 --> 01:13:47.048 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's time for you to move away.

877
01:13:53.471 --> 01:13:54.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[wheelbarrow thuds]

878
01:14:13.240 --> 01:14:14.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is everything all right?

879
01:14:18.079 --> 01:14:19.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can't find Papa.

880
01:14:20.122 --> 01:14:22.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He went on a different work duty
with some of the men,

881
01:14:22.833 --> 01:14:24.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and they haven't come back.

882
01:14:28.297 --> 01:14:29.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sniffles]

883
01:14:34.053 --> 01:14:35.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got some bad news, too.

884
01:14:36.806 --> 01:14:37.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm going away.

885
